        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 6:34PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 634 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Truckton, or 27 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving
northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ellicott and Truckton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
